rComments: Best prof at uoft.
Hands down the best lectures I'll ever have. Not only very clear and interesting, but hilarious too. Breaks my heart he only teaches one course, I'll miss him.

Yeooo so I didnt actually take psl 300 or even go to uoft but I went to a walk in clinic this guy was my doctor and successfully diagnosed me. I googled the yute turns out hes a lecturer too. I should let yall know that he probably a lit prof but he a good doctor too and my experience in the walk in shows hes logical, and has case experience.

He has a bit disorganized slides and sometimes talks really fast but otherwise a really amazing professor since he cared a lot about his students. Held a review session before each midterm and held a career talk. Really appreciate him and is inspiring
Fantastic guy!! Interesting material and he is super funny and engaging. Best prof i had this semester by far

Amazing professor. Dhillon really goes over and beyond to help students - whether that's with understanding material/concepts or giving you more info on careers in the medical field. He usually recycles many of his past exam questions and his lectures are funny and engaging.

Dr. Dhillion is an amazing prof, he made PSL300 enjoyable for me and he's hands down the best prof I've had at uoft. Would 100% recommend taking his class, he is just a humble person and truly loves teaching. He does talk fast sometimes but that's only because he gets excited about the content. His tests are fair and repetitive from past midterms!

Hands down THE BEST PROF I have ever had at UofT. UofT really needs more people like him. He felt more like a friend than a prof or a doctor or somebody who is "just doing their job". You could tell he really cared about us and our understanding of the concepts. He always went out of his way to do what was best for us.

Living Legend. He does speak fast but it's b/c he gets excited about the material and is very enthusiastic to teach class. Provides great explanations and does go over concepts twice (considering he goes so fast). Very passionate about teaching and a helpful person outside class as well. Would love to take another class with him.

Dr. Dhillon is an amazing lecturer. The material is interesting and lectures are actually fun--he's pretty funny. Really emphasizes what's important to know for his midterm. Approachable if you have questions. Buy the test pack and do the questions, his midterms are repeats. Don't worry about the textbook and don't cram!!

Honestly amazing. Such a good lecturer, explained everything perfectly and gives really good anecdotes to help you remember stuff. He's also a doctor so he applies everything you learn to real life scenarios. He really cares about his students and goes out of his way to help. Literally best prof at this school.
amazing prof.

His lectures are organized. He speaks too fast. He should consider becoming a rapper. I guess it's too late for that, since he is doing his residency. Also, really funny guy. He knows his anatomy really well, just what you would expect from a person who teaches physiology.

One of the BEST profs I've ever had in my undergrad! I left every single lecture feeling like I really learned something. Not only that, but I genuinely looked forward to class and would be upset to skip it because of a timetable conflict. He's super funny and engages the 1000+ student class so well.

Sandeep Dhillon is AMAZING. Although he does talk very quick, he knows how to explain concepts in a clear and concise manner. He engages well with the students by either making jokes or asking if anyone is confused throughout the lecture. He also goes above and beyond to help kids who are interested in medicine since he is a doctor himself.

Best prof ever! He's super hilarious and very entertaining during lectures. He's also a practicing doctor, so he gives short anecdotes about his patients during lectures, which is really interesting. I wish he could teach more sections in the course!
this is my second review. he's the best prof ever. PSL students miss him. 10/10.

Best prof I've ever had at UofT. He truly cares. I tell everyone about the impact his teaching has had on my education! I've compared every PSL lecture to his, and none has compared. He's super helpful and provides all information in a logical and applicable manner with a clinical viewpoint. idk how he's so HOT and this accomplished, what a gem.
Best UofT Prof. Explains concepts well and reinforces teachings with great and often hilarious clinical scenarios. DIME is right.

Dr Dhillon is honestly the best prof I've ever had. He makes each class enjoyable by and gives many clinical examples. He is super approachable after class and very humble. He's also hilarious in class. Everything you need to know is in his lectures, make sure you link concepts and you'll do great! :)
if you have dhillon u will be blessed for life ez 90+
great prof

Dr. Dhillon is the exact young/passionate professor U of T needs. Physiology is not an easy course but he does a beautiful job in teaching it. Considering how "bad" PSL tests/exams are, if you listen to him carefully and do your best in understanding him, you'll realize that the test is extremely fair and quite frankly easy to follow.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Dr. Dhillon has been my best professor thus far. He is Hilarious. Legend is right. Gives clinical scenarios to discuss further understanding. LOVE HIM!

Lectures were entertaining and very clear. PSL300 is a dense course, and Professor Dhillon does a great job at throughly explaining all the material necessary for the test and his test was fair. However, lectures were a bit too fast paced and would sometimes run past the hour. He also held a research seminar outside of classtime.

Sandeep was hands down the best prof I have had so far at U of T. An amazing lecturer and he really explains things in an understandable way (probably has to do with the fact that he's also a doctor and has to explain health issues to his patients all the time). Also HE IS A DIME. 10/10. So hot.
Lectures were fast-paced due to the sheer-amount of material for this course but his recordings helped more than the actual textbook. Love this man (also he's fine)
Dr. Dhillon makes PSL300 a very interesting course. You can tell he is very passionate about the material he teaches and presents it in a way that is very easy to understand. Great Prof!

He is an amazing lecturer. His slides have the perfect balance between text and images, and he explains them so well in class. I could literally hear his voice in my head saying "PTH takes calcium from the bone and throws it at the blood" during my exam. He also extended his office hours and held a two hour review session the week of the midterm.

This guy is truly a legend. He makes every lecture so much fun between his passion and in depth explanations to his hilarious comments every so often. He makes you feel comfortable in a fairly difficult course. Very fair tests.
He's the best prof I've ever had and honestly, he's probably the best prof I'll ever have. He's really interested in his own material and you can tell. He's also very interesting.

Simply put, Dr. Dhillon is a legend. Turns what might easily have been a dry and overwhelming course into the the highlight of the week. Relates his professional experiences to theoretical concepts. Sure, the course is tough, but his teaching makes it worthwhile.
Dr. Dhillon was the best professor I have ever had in my life. He made me love physiology and Understand it very well.

Professor Dhillon is everything you could ask for in a professor. He is a doctor, smart, funny, and knows how to make the material engaging and memorable. It seems to be a joint consensus that his lectures were amazing.
